        <p>After establishing the supremacy of consciousness above all, Lord Krishna says the only way we can win over desires/ Kama is we need to concentrate on the realization of self rather than on senses/mind/buddhi. Restrain the senses right from the beginning and divert the senses from enjoying the sense objects towards the self-realization. Reading holy scriptures, doing meditation listening to holy music will help in this endeavor, keeping the senses always engaged in the work will also help. Parallelly change the mind into thinking good thoughts about the realization of self. Working selflessly without any desires will help and do not give any spare time for the mind to think negative thoughts.</p>

