        <p>Arjuna says to Lord Krishna that what he has seen just now is the supreme truth which can be known by the scriptures. God is the only support of this universe. God is imperishable and is the preserver of Dharma. God is the everlasting supreme soul. The word purusa is used here for God. Samkhya yoga distinguishes Purusa and Prakriti the spiritual and material nature.</p>

