        <p>The metaphor of rivers merging into oceans is given here. All rivers start independently at different places just like human beings. They travel fastly with full energy like children and youth. Then at maturity, they calm down flow slowly and then at the end rivers merge into oceans. In the same way, human beings start uniquely, live their lives and in the end, they all merge into the mighty ocean called God. Arjuna could see all of this before his eyes as Krishna showed to him all fate of all the kings who are standing before him. All the kings might be having an independent existence as of now but in the war, the fate of all of them is merging into God.</p>

